[BUGS]
- In some places, LOD loses resolution as camera gets closer
	- Seen with these params in flat areas
	   	const uint32_t TERRAIN_QUAD_RESOLUTION { 64 };
    	const float TERRAIN_SPLIT_FACTOR  { 1.5f };
    	const uint32_t TERRAIN_MAX_LOD { 20 };
    	const uint32_t NUM_QUAD_TREE_NODES  { 4 };
    	const uint32_t GPU_TILE_BUFFER_SIZE  { 1024 };


[Features]
├─ API Agnostic Rendering


├─ XBOX Controller Support

├─ Shader Recompile
└── Recompile shader changes on the fly

├─  Terrain shading
├──  Generate heightmap normals using sobel filter
├───  Dependency between heightmap data and normal data during gpu tile production
└──  Hardcode directional light in shaders from quick and dirty shading

├─ Debug Rendering
├── Don't use lines -- lines suck
└── Smarter caching and creation of vertex data

├─ Text Rendering
└──  Use freetype-gl library (/sigh, jake)

├─ Frustum Culling
└──  Not perfect, get some false positives on edge of screen

├─ Planet
└──  Spherical deformation

├─ Chunked LOD
├── Skirts
├── Better control of when LOD switches happen
└── Morphing between LODs
